The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Srirupa Chowdhury

 Class X, Mahadevi Birla Girls? HS School, and finalist, Classmate Young Author Contest 2004

 Certainly. Since the protagonists are teenagers and they talk of friendship, school and pressure of exams, we find it easy to identify with them. Fantasy is also a favourite genre of our times. So many who do not touch story books otherwise, read Harry Potter due to peer pressure. Whatever the reason may be, the fact that it makes them read shows that Potter is doing the job. I read an average of 10 books a month. Besides developing my writing style, the habit has made me the person I am. In my class of 40, four-five of us are serious book-lovers. One needs guidance on the kind of books suitable for one?s age to develop a love of reading at the right time.




